Package: ILAMM
Type: Package
Title: Nonconvex Regularized Robust Regression via I-LAMM Algorithm
Version: 1.0.0
Author: Xiaoou Pan, Qiang Sun, Wen-Xin Zhou
Maintainer: Xiaoou Pan <xip024@ucsd.edu>, 
            Qiang Sun <qsun@utstat.toronto.edu>, 
            Wen-Xin Zhou <wez243@ucsd.edu>
Description: A C++ implementation of I-LAMM algorithm to compute regularized Huber regression. 
             The choice of penalty functions includes the l1-norm (Lasso), the smoothly clipped absolute deviation (SCAD) and the minimax concave penalty (MCP).
             Two tuning parameters lambda (for penalty) and tau (for Huber loss) can be either user-specified or calibrated by k-fold cross-validation. 
             Other options include adding an intercept term into the model and modifying parameters in the I-LAMM algorithm.
